items.title: Parity bit - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
A parity bit, or check bit is a bit added to the end of a string of binary code that 
indicates whether the number of bits in the string with the value one is even or 
odd.

items.title: Parity-check matrix - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
In coding theory, a parity-check matrix of a linear block code C is a matrix which 
describes the linear relations that the components of a codeword must satisfy.
